"children":[
"Pituitary Adenomas"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s7_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a038bc",
"children":[
"Pituitary adenomas are benign tumors that originate from one of the different anterior pituitary cell types. They are classified based on size as microadenomas (<10 mm) or macroadenomas (≥10 mm)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3ef109",
"children":[
"Pituitary adenomas become symptomatic by two different mechanisms:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a140fc",
"children":[
"mass effect causing hypopituitarism (anterior hormone deficiencies more common than posterior), headaches, visual disturbance/visual field defects, and cranial nerve dysfunction"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"827db4",
"children":[
"endocrine hyperfunction caused by excess secretion by the tumor (most commonly prolactinomas)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_f03"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4902a9",
"children":[
"The pituitary gland is enlarged diffusely in untreated primary hypothyroidism and during normal pregnancies."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s7_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"dc7e47",
"children":[
"Most incidentally noted pituitary masses in asymptomatic patients are benign, nonfunctional pituitary adenomas."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"338453",
"children":[
"Obtain dedicated pituitary MRI."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fe6266",
"children":[
"Assess possible pituitary hypersecretion (measure prolactin and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"insulin-like growth factor-1",
"children":[
"IGF-1"
]
},
")."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"af0f09",
"children":[
"Screen patients for hypopituitarism with pituitary tumors regardless of symptoms with measurement of:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"36aa84",
"children":[
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"follicle-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"FSH"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"luteinizing hormone",
"children":[
"LH"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f375dc",
"children":[
"cortisol"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7793fa",
"children":[
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thyroid-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"TSH"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"free thyroxine",
"children":[
"T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"4"
]
}
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9a56d4",
"children":[
"total testosterone (men)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"18fbb9",
"children":[
"A menstrual history can assess for hypogonadotropic hypogonadism in premenopausal women."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9b2a44",
"children":[
"Testing for Cushing disease is not necessary in the absence of symptoms."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_s7_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_f04"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5fe254",
"children":[
"Psychotropic agents, tricyclic antidepressants, antiseizure medications, metoclopramide and domperidone, calcium channel blockers, methyldopa, opioids, and protease inhibitors can cause hyperprolactinemia."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e95ea3",
"children":[
"The prolactin level influenced by drugs and other nonprolactinoma conditions is usually <150 ng/mL."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2b6d71",
"children":[
"Obtain a pregnancy test in all women with hyperprolactinemia."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5feae6",
"children":[
"Obtain a serum TSH level in all patients with hyperprolactinemia (hypothyroidism can cause hyperprolactinemia)."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s7_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"60cc65",
"children":[
"Choose ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"observation"
]
},
" for women with microprolactinoma and normal menses or for patients with nonfunctioning pituitary microadenomas."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"096014",
"children":[
"Choose a dopamine agonist (cabergoline preferred to bromocriptine) for symptomatic prolactinoma."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fceee3",
"children":[
"Choose ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"surgery"
]
},
" for adenomas secreting ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"growth hormone",
"children":[
"GH"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"adrenocorticotropic hormone",
"children":[
"ACTH"
]
},
","
]
},
" or TSH; for adenomas associated with mass effect, visual field defects, or hypopituitarism; and for prolactinomas unresponsive to dopamine agonists."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s7_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"acf9c3",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 32-year-old woman has a 4-mm hypointense area in the pituitary gland discovered incidentally on an MRI. Medical history, including menstrual function, and physical examination are normal. The serum prolactin level and thyroid function tests are normal."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8d768a",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose an incidental nonfunctioning pituitary adenoma. For management, repeat the MRI in 1 year."
]
}
]
}
]
},
